{
  "doc_id": "28738",
  "text": "Manhattan distance is a special case of the Minkowski distance at m = 1. Like its parent, Manhattan is sensitive to outliers. When this distance measure is used in clustering algorithms, the shape of clusters is hyper-rectangular [CITATION_1] . A study by Perlibakas demonstrated that a modified version of this distance measure is among the best distance measures for PCA-based face recognition [CITATION_2] . This measure is defined as d man ¼ P n i¼1 jx i À y i j.",
